{
    "name": "maya",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "private": true,
    "description": "Maya is a peer-reviewed platform designed to bridge the gap between specialists and non-specialist in the climate field. It offers a unique space where specialist data is synthesized and presented in an accessible, informative manner. Our goal is to empower non-specialists with reliable and understandable climate knowledge, facilitating informed decisions and greater awareness. Maya leverages advanced data visualization techniques and collaborative tools to make complex environmental information easily digestible for everyone.",
    "author": "Jack Robetson is an information designer. Who explores how storytelling and narratives can be used to examine complex systems, like economics, politics, and much more! His work is based on the idea that playfulness and curiosity can lead to insights about the world around us. Jack is interested in using research and design thinking to create experiences that engage people with the systems that shape our lives.",
    "keywords": [
        "gatsby",
        "climate communication",
        "knowledge sharing",
        "peer-reviewed content",
        "specialist insights",
        "environmental data",
        "accessible information",
        "climate change education",
        "sustainable practices",
        "community engagement",
        "climate science",
        "data visualization",
        "environmental awareness",
        "interdisciplinary collaboration",
        "climate policy",
        "environmental research"
    ],
